item.title: Paropsisterna brunnea
item.dc:creator: suzanne
item.description: A green larva from my previous observation was kept and these photos are of its transition from a larvae into a beetle. It stopped eating on 3 March and shed its skin and became a pupa (as in first photo here) on the evening of 6 March. The last three photos were taken on the 15 March as it emerged as a beetle, which has been thought by Martin Lagerwey to be Paropsisterna brunnea.

item.title: Myrmecia spp.
item.dc:creator: suzanne
item.description: This young eucalypt tree had been surrounded by a plastic surround (that was put on when the tree was planted). We saw that the area between the trunk of the tree and the plastic had been filled with dirt to about 8" or so up the bag. So we removed the plastic and discovered that the dirt was a bullant nest and they were not happy with the destruction of their home. I took just a few photos, then after five minutes or so went back and got more photos when the bullants were occupied collecting their pupa family members and taking them underground.
